      <li><u>Impact Grenade</u>: Impact grenades are a great tool for allowing movement through the map or creating vision for the team. They aren't good at dealing damage however so keep them for the previously mentioned purpose.</li>
      <li><u>Deployable Shield</u>: This is a great gadget for creating choke points where the enemy is forced to vault over, giving you an advantage. </li>
    </ul>
  <% elsif @operator.name == "Pulse" %>
    <ul>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/29">UMP-45</a></u>: UMP-45 is a standard submachine gun that is most accurate in small bursts. This is a pretty good gun for wallbanging people who don't know you're there.</li>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/43">M1014</a></u>: Standard shotgun that's pretty good for holding corners. Due to how Pulse plays, the shotgun can be very good for opening holes above an enemy and just killing them quickly before they realize what happened.</li>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/38">M45 MEUSOC</a></u>: A solid pistol with high per bullet damage and little recoil with a muzzle break on. This gun is great for killing a downed enemy in one shot and quick switching to it if the enemy is only a shot or two away from dying and your primary is empty. However, you will find this gun lacking in extended fights.</li>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/44">5.7 USG</a></u>: Another solid pistol. It has less damage than the M45 but has the highest mag size in the game at 21. This should be taken if you are incredibly confident at your ability to hit headshots.</li>
      <li><u>Barbed wire</u>: Barbed wire is an amazing tool as it slows and hurts an enemy's mobility. This can be the difference between life and death sometimes for you and your team while also giving you information when someone is around.</li>
      <li><u>Nitro Cell(aka C4)</u>: Highly recommeneded for Pulse due to his ability to set a trap with this by placing it near an entrance that is highly used and waiting until you detect someone.</li>
    </ul>
  <% elsif @operator.name == "Twitch" %>
    <h3>Loadout</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/10">F2</a></u>: The F2 is a great assault rifle due to its high per bullet damage and rate of fire, while also being extremely accurate in small bursts. This is Twitch's go-to gun for most situations.</li>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/8">417</a></u>: The 417 is the gun for all you people who wanna be Glaz but he was already picked. With a bit less damage than Glaz's rifle, it still does a lot of per bullet damage and has a much higher rate of fire. This is a good gun to go if you'll be playing back and holding or cover angles for the most part.</li>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/34">SG-CQB</a></u>: Shotguns should usually not be run on an attacker unless they have a rapid fire secondary or if you're rushing. You don't really rush on Twitch though.</li>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/39">P9</a></u>: Unlike your other secondary, the P9 much lower damage but is extremly accurate with a muzzle break and has a larger mag size. Go with this if you aren't comfortable with the LFP586 or you want a more reliable secondary fo frantic moments.</li>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/35">LFP586</a></u>: Like previously mentioned, the LFP586 is a high damage secondary but has some of the worst recoil in the game. This is a good weapon with very well placed shots but can be difficult to do if you aren't used to it.</li>
      <li><u>Breaching Charge</u>: Breaching charge is a good gadget to run in any situation as it allows you to make a walkable hole in any soft wall that defenders forgot to reinforce.</li>
      <li><u>Claymore</u>: This is a great gadget on Twitch due to the fact that you will most likely be on your drone most of the time. I would recommend it if you plan to play more defensively.</li>
    </ul>
  <% elsif @operator.name == "Doc" %>
    <h3>Loadout</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/21">MP5</a></u>: The MP5 is a great gun for most defenders as it has a good amount of damage, nice recoil, and a good mag size. This can kill anyone easily with a few well placed shots.</li>
      <li><u><a href="/guns/36">P90</a></u>: The P90 is another good weapon with a higher than average rate of fire and is pretty accurate. This is good gun for all ranges and recommended if you aren't comfortable with landing the first few shots on the MP5.</li>
